<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING PUMP: VICKERS (LUK) V10NF AND V20NF - INSTALL - BELT DRIVEN PUMP
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>BELT DRIVEN PUMP</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position pump and fasten to pump bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install pressure line, return line and pump supply (remote mounted reservoir) on pump.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install pump pulley on pump shaft and tighten shaft bolt to 15 to 20 ft-lbs. (20 to 27
                Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install pump belt and tension belt to specifications. Refer to GROUP 12 - ENGINE, Cooling
                section in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten all pump mounting bracket fasteners to 30 to 38 ft-lbs. (41 to 52 Nm).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill system with approved power steering fluid. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s05005s_22.xml" xrefid="hl0500504">LUBRICATION/BLEED SYSTEM</hotlnk>
                on this page.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bleed system.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Recheck fluid level after bleeding system.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
